---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Portfolio | lisAIconsulting';
const pageDescription =
  'Selected examples of AI-enabled workflow design, automation, and business process improvement.';

const n8nImages = [
  {
    src: '/images/portfolio/n8n-1-workflow-overview.png',
    alt: 'n8n workflow overview showing the defect intake automation flow.',
    caption: 'Workflow overview: the automation captures intake details and routes them into a structured tracking flow.',
  },
  {
    src: '/images/portfolio/n8n-2-form-example.png',
    alt: 'Example of the intake form used to capture defect details.',
    caption: 'Structured intake: the form standardizes what is captured at the start of the process.',
  },
  {
    src: '/images/portfolio/n8n-3-sheet-output.png',
    alt: 'Google Sheet output populated by the n8n workflow.',
    caption: 'Operational output: submissions are appended into a shared tracking structure for visibility and follow-up.',
  },
];

const gptImages = [$1];
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main class="portfolio-page">
      <section class="hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Portfolio</p>
        <h1>Examples of practical AI, automation, and workflow design</h1>
        <p class="intro">
          These examples reflect the kind of work I can design and deliver: structured intake,
          process improvement, and lightweight automation that solve real business problems
          without adding unnecessary complexity.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="portfolio-grid" aria-label="Portfolio examples">
        <div class="section-intro">
          <h2>Selected work</h2>
          <p>
            Two examples are shown below: one focused on workflow automation and one focused on
            structured AI-assisted intake. Together they show how I approach process design,
            operational clarity, and practical execution.
          </p>
        </div>
        <article class="case-study">
          <div class="case-header">
            <p class="case-kicker">Example 1</p>
            <h2>n8n Defect Intake & Tracking Automation</h2>
          </div>

          <p>
            This workflow demonstrates how manual intake can be streamlined into a more consistent,
            auditable process. A form submission captures defect information, routes it through a
            structured workflow, and appends the result to a Google Sheet for tracking and follow-up.
          </p>

          <div class="detail-grid">
            <div>
              <h3>Business problem</h3>
              <p>
                Defect reporting is often inconsistent, incomplete, and difficult to track across
                teams. This creates rework, slows triage, and reduces visibility into priorities.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3>Approach</h3>
              <p>
                Designed an n8n workflow that standardizes intake, captures key issue details, and
                pushes the result into a shared tracking structure that supports triage and reporting.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3>Value</h3>
              <p>
                Improves consistency, reduces manual handoffs, and creates a cleaner operational
                record for defect management.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="callout">
            <strong>What it demonstrates:</strong>
            translating a manual business process into a lightweight automation with clearer intake,
            better visibility, and repeatable execution.
          </div>

          <div class="demo-block">
            <h3>Demo walkthrough</h3>
            <p>
              This example shows a simple intake-to-tracking flow: information is captured in a
              consistent format, routed through n8n, and recorded in a shared structure that
              supports triage and follow-up.
            </p>

            <div class="image-grid image-grid-three">
              {n8nImages.map((image) => (
                <figure class="image-card">
                  <img src={image.src} alt={image.alt} loading="lazy" />
                  <figcaption>{image.caption}</figcaption>
                </figure>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="case-study">
          <div class="case-header">
            <p class="case-kicker">Example 2</p>
            <h2>Business Intake & Prioritization GPT</h2>
          </div>

          <p>
            This example shows how a custom GPT can be used as a business-facing intake assistant.
            Rather than jumping directly to a solution, it asks targeted follow-up questions,
            identifies missing information, and produces a structured summary that supports faster
            triage and clearer decision-making.
          </p>

          <div class="detail-grid">
            <div>
              <h3>Business problem</h3>
              <p>
                Teams often submit requests that are incomplete, vague, or missing context such as
                urgency, impact, owner, or dependencies. That leads to back-and-forth, poor intake
                quality, and slower prioritization.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3>Approach</h3>
              <p>
                Designed a GPT to behave like a business intake analyst: ask concise clarifying
                questions first, then generate a structured request summary with business need,
                impact, urgency, constraints, and recommended next step.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3>Value</h3>
              <p>
                Converts unstructured requests into decision-ready inputs, improving intake quality
                while reducing clarification cycles and operational friction.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="callout">
            <strong>What it demonstrates:</strong>
            designing AI-assisted workflows that support business process improvement rather than
            novelty. The focus is on structure, clarity, and usable output.
          </div>

          <div class="demo-block">
            <h3>Demo walkthrough</h3>
            <p>
              In this example, a vague request about email cleanup is transformed into a structured
              summary with business need, impact, urgency, risks, and next step. The screenshots
              below show the progression from raw request to organized output.
            </p>

            <div class="image-grid">
              {gptImages.map((image) => (
                <figure class="image-card">
                  <img src={image.src} alt={image.alt} loading="lazy" />
                  <figcaption>{image.caption}</figcaption>
                </figure>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="closing">
        <h2>How I approach this work</h2>
        <p>
          I focus on business-ready solutions: clarify the problem, define the workflow, reduce
          friction, and use the right level of automation to improve execution. In some cases that
          means a simple automation. In others, it means designing a structured AI interaction that
          helps teams intake and organize work more effectively.
        </p>
        <p>
          If your team needs help shaping a workflow, improving intake, or turning a manual process
          into a more consistent operating model, I’d be glad to discuss it.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  :root {
    --page-max: 1120px;
    --text: #1f2937;
    --muted: #5b6472;
    --surface: #ffffff;
    --surface-soft: #f7f9fc;
    --border: #d9e2ec;
    --accent-soft: #eef4ff;
  }

  .portfolio-page {
    width: min(calc(100% - 2rem), var(--page-max));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 0 4rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .hero {
    padding: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .eyebrow,
  .case-kicker {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .intro {
    max-width: 760px;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .portfolio-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .section-intro {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .section-intro h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .section-intro p {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 760px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .case-study,
  .closing {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 22px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.05);
  }

  .case-header h2,
  .closing h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  .case-study > p,
  .closing p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .detail-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .detail-grid div {
    background: var(--surface-soft);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .detail-grid h3,
  .demo-block h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
  }

  .detail-grid p,
  .demo-block p,
  figcaption {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .callout {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    background: var(--accent-soft);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 12px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .demo-block {
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .image-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .image-grid-three {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .image-card {
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--surface-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 14px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .image-card img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .image-card figcaption {
    padding: 0.9rem 1rem 1rem;
  }

  .closing {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .detail-grid,
    .image-grid,
    .image-grid-three {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
